data.title: Actors Born on March 3
data.meta_description: Famous birthdays in film and TV for the 3rd of March. Browse actors, actresses and directors that were born on March 3.
data.text:
William Charles Macready, British actor, manager, and diarist, born in London, England (d. 1873)

Adelaide Neilson, English stage actress (The Hunchback), born in Leeds, England (d. 1880)

Florence Auer, American actress (Eradicating Aunty), born in Albany, New York (d. 1962)

Edmund Lowe, American actor (Black Sheep, Good Sam, Dillinger, Hot Pepper), born in San Jose, California (d. 1971)

Beatrice Wood, American artist, ceramist and editor (The Blind Man, inspiration for Titanic film character Rose), born in San Francisco, California (d. 1998)

1893 Bill Nestell, American actor (Dangerous Venture, Buckskin Frontier), born in San Francisco, California (d. 1966)

Juanita Hansen, American actress (Fast Company, Broadway Love), born in Des Moines, Iowa (d. 1961)

1895 Robert Gordon, American silent film actor (Hearts and Spangles; King of the Pack), born in Belleville, Kansas (d. 1971)

Edna Best, British actress (Key, Calendar, Escape, Intermezzo), born in Hove, England (d. 1974)

1900 Ruby Dandridge [Ruby Jean Butler], American actress (Father of the Bride), born in Wichita, Kansas (d. 1987)

Gilbert Adrian [Greenberg], American costume designer (MGM films, The Wizard of Oz), born in Naugatuck, Connecticut (d. 1959)

Donald Novis, British-American singer and actor (Monte Carlo; The Singing Plumber), born in Hastings, East Sussex, England (d. 1966)

Canada Lee [Leonard Canegata], African-American actor (Lost Boundaries), born in New York City (d. 1952)

Kittens Reichert [Catherine Alma Reichert], American silent screen child actor [House of Cards, Les Misérables], born in Yonkers, New York (d. 1990)

Jean Harlow

American actress and 1930s' sex goddess (Dinner at 8; Bombshell), born in Kansas City, Missouri

Martin Ritt, American actor and director (The Spy Who Came In from the Cold, Slugger's Wife, End of the Game), born in New York City (d. 1990)

James Doohan, Canadian actor (Star Trek), born in Vancouver, British Columbia (d. 2005)

Diana Barrymore, American actress (Nightmare, Lady Courageous, Fired Wife), born in New York City (d. 1960)

Barney Martin, American actor, comedy writer and NYPD detective (Seinfeld), born in Queens, New York (d. 2005)

Lilian Velez, Filipno actress (Sa Kabukiran), born in Cebu City, Philippine Islands (d. 1948)

Piet Bambergen, Dutch comic and actor (The Mounties; The Mad Adventures of Sherlock Jones), born in Amsterdam, Netherlands (d. 1996)

Alfredo Landa, Spanish actor (The Crach, Sinatra), born in Pamplona, Spain (d. 2013)

1933 Marco Antonio Muñoz, Mexican Latin pop singer (Que Murmurmen; Escandallo), and actor (Sinful), born in Guadalajara, Jalisco, Mexico

Gia Scala [Josephine Scoglio], British-American actress (Garment Jungle; I Aim at the Stars; Angry Hills), born in Liverpool, England (d. 1972)

Bobby Driscoll, American Academy Juvenile Award-winning actor (Song Of The South; The Window), born in Cedar Rapids, Iowa (d. 1968)

Bill Frindall, English cricket scorer and statistician (BBC, "the Bearded Wonder"), born in Epsom, England (d. 2009)

Owen Spencer-Thomas, English broadcaster, journalist and Anglican clergyman

Roger Swaybill, actor/writer (Porky's II, Breaking Point)

Hattie Winston, actress (Nurse, Electric Company), born in Greenville, Mississippi

Byron MacGregor, newscaster

Re Styles [Shirley Macleod], Dutch-American actress (Space Is The Place), designer, and rock vocalist (The Tubes, 1976-79), born in the Netherlands (d. 2022)

1950 Tim Kazurinsky, American comic actor and screenwriter (SNL, 1980-84; Police Academy 2, 3, 4), born in Johnstown, Pennsylvania

Miranda Richardson, Southport England, actress (Damage, Crying Game)

Knut Nærum, Norwegian comedian

1961 Mary Page Keller, American actress (Ryan's Hope, Duet), born in Monterey Park, California

Sophia Aliberti, Greek actress and TV presenter

Laura Harring

Mexican-American actress (Mulholland Drive; General Hospital) and Miss USA 1985, born in Los Mochis, Sinaloa, Mexico

1964 Lisa Ann Poggi, American actress (Candyman; Loving), born in Grand Rapids Michigan

Fernando Colunga, Mexican actor and director (Pasión, Ladrón que roba a ladrón), born in Mexico City

Elizabeth Cheshire, actress (Jill-Sunshine), born in Burbank, California

Brian Cox, English physicist and musician (BBC Wonders of... series), born in Oldham, England

Julie Bowen

American actress (Claire Dunphy - Modern Family), born in Baltimore, Maryland

Christian Oliver, actor (Baby Sitters Club, Brian-Saved by the Bell)

Matthew Marsden, British actor (Atlas Shrugged; Coronation Street, 1997-98), born in West Bromwich, Staffordshire, England

David Faustino, actor (I Had 3 Wives, Bud-Married With Children), born in Los Angeles, California

1974 Jared Rushton, actor (Big, Honey I Shrank the Kids)

1974 Paula Malai Ali, Malaysian-Bruneian TV Presenter and Actress

Ronan Keating

Irish pop singer (Boyzone - "Words"; "No Matter What"; solo -"When You Say Nothing At All"), radio host, and television personality, born in Bayside, Dublin, Ireland

Alex Zane, English comedian

1979 Patrick Renna, American actor

Eugene [Kim Yoo-Jin], South Korean K-pop singer (S.E.S.) and actress (A Hundred Year Legacy), born in Seoul, South Korea

1981 Sung Yu Ri, South Korean K-pop singer (Fin.K.L.) and actress (Hong Gil-dong), born in Tübingen, West Germany

Jessica Biel

American actress (Mary Camden in 7th Heaven), born in Ely, Minnesota
